  "body": "### Description\r\n\r\n*Type*: Bug\r\n\r\n*Summary*: When \"Advanced\" section is opened and user has scrolled to the top to see his avatar, pressing the \"Edit\" button causes the screen to be scrolled down: \r\n\r\n<img src=\"https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/7532782/41649291-91c9c398-747b-11e8-9aaa-2856bc7a37ea.png\" width=\"200\">\r\n\r\nIn result, the user needs to scroll up manually to edit the name or change profile. \r\n\r\n#### Expected behavior\r\nBasically I'd like to have screen automatically scrolled to the top (if it's not already) if the \"Edit\" is pressed. This means:\r\n1. When screen is scrolled to the top, pressing \"Edit\" does not scroll it down\r\n2. When screen is scrolled so that profile or username are not visible, pressing \"Edit\" should scroll it automatically to the top\r\n\r\n#### Actual behavior\r\nScreen is scrolled down when \"Edit\" is pressed.\r\n\r\n### Reproduction\r\n\r\n**Scenario A:**\r\n- Open Status\r\n- Go to Profile\r\n- Open Advance section\r\n- Scroll to the top\r\n- Press Edit\r\n-> Screen should not be scrolled down\r\n\r\n**Scenario B:**\r\n- Open Status\r\n- Go to Profile\r\n- Open Advanced section\r\n- Scroll down\r\n- Press Edit\r\n-> Screen should be scrolled to the top to show avatar and username input\r\n\r\n### Additional Information\r\n* Status version: 0.9.20\r\n* Operating System: Android, iOS\r\n",
